  <thing id="manPWGlIm5" name="Gleaming Imprisonment" description="Twisting the reflections around your blade, you mark an enemy with it and imprison them in a sphere of mirrors. When you initiate this maneuver, make a melee attack. If you hit, it deals normal weapon damage plus an additional 4d6 damage, and the struck creature must succeed at a Reflex save (DC 15 + your initiation modifier) or be trapped within a sphere of two-sided mirrors that forms around them for a number of rounds equal to your initiation modifier. While the sphere of mirrors exists, a trapped creature cannot move or be moved from its space by any means (including teleportation), target or be targeted by any other creature or object (except for objects it is attending, carrying, or using), and is immune to area-of-effect attacks and effects that originate from outside its space. Such effects originating from the trapped creature affect only its own space." compset="PWManuever" summary="Strike - Make a melee attack, trap struck creature in a sphere of mirrors." uniqueness="useronce">
